data.content:
## What Changed

In .NET 10, `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **OpenAPI.NET v2.x**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1. This introduces several breaking changes:

| .NET 9 (OpenAPI.NET v1) | .NET 10 (OpenAPI.NET v2) |
|---|---|
| `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. | Removed — use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` |
| `schema.Example = new OpenApiString(...)` | `schema.Example = JsonValue.Create(...)` |
| `schema.Nullable = true/false` | Removed — use `Type` flags enum with `JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` inherits `Dictionary` | Has a `Schemes` property instead |

## Fixed Code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;        // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // JsonValue.Create instead of new OpenApiString
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    // OpenApiSecurityRequirement no longer extends Dictionary — use Schemes property
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { Schemes = { [oAuthScheme] = scopes } }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
            {
                // Nullable property removed; clear the Null flag from the Type enum
                property.Value.Type = property.Value.Type & ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of fixes:
1. **`using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any`** → **`using System.Text.Json.Nodes`**
2. **`new OpenApiString("1.0")`** → **`JsonValue.Create("1.0")`**
3. **`new() { [scheme] = scopes }`** → **`new() { Schemes = { [scheme] = scopes } }`**
4. **`property.Value.Nullable = false`** → **`property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null`**
